#####################################
#####							#####
##### Configuration explanation #####
#####							#####
#####################################

~~~ configured ~~~
Expected value: boolean
Default value: false
Description: If this value is set to false, the plugin won't work. Please set this value to true after you have configured the plugin.

~~~ database.host ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value: localhost
Description: The address of the database

~~~ database.port ~~~
Expected value: Integer
Default value: 3306
Description: The database port

~~~ database.username ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value: root
Description: The account username which is used to connect to the database

~~~ database.password ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value:
Description: The account password which is used to connect to the database

~~~ database.database ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value: database
Description: The database which the plugin will use after connecting to the database

~~~ database.table_prefix ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value: mutesystem
Description: The prefix which is put in front of the table in which the information is stored

~~~ database.use_ssl ~~~
Expected value: Boolean
Default value: true
Description: The database attempts to use SSL to encrypt the data transfer

~~~ database.require_ssl ~~~
Expected value: Boolean
Default value: false
Description: A connection will only be established if the database supports SSL encryption

~~~ cache.cache_time ~~~
Expected value: Integer
Default value: 20
Unit: seconds
Description: The amount of time during which the data which is cached is valid.
Recommendation: Set this value to a higher value if you are only using this plugin on one server. If you are using it on multiple servers at the same time, using a low value is recommended.

~~~ cache.automatic_cache_clearing.activated ~~~
Expected value: Boolean
Default value: true
Description: Enabled if after n seconds the invalid cache data should be remove from memory or not
Recommendation: Activate this if you have a lot of players on the server or if you experience memoroy issues

~~~ cache.automatic_cache_clearing.interval ~~~
Expected value: Long
Default value: 500
Description: The interval at which the invalid cache data is removed from memory

~~~ language ~~~
Expected value: String
Default value: en_US
Description: The language which is used by the plugin
Information: Do not add the .json file ending to the value. It is automatically added when loading the language.
Adding a new language: If you want to add a new language just copy one of the existing language files and rename the new file. Then edit the values to your language. It can then be used like any language provided by the plugin.

~~~ command.mute_history.display_limit ~~~
Expected value: Integer
Default value: 10
Description: The amount of history values which are displayed.

~~~ block_command_execution_when_muted ~~~
Expected value: Boolean
Default value: false
Description: Prevent a player from executing all commands when being muted


