##### Commands #####
#####		   #####
####################

~~~ mute ~~~
Permission: mutesystem.mute
Syntax: /mute (target) [reason]
Description: Mute a player

~~~ mutehistory ~~~
Permission: mutesystem.mutehistory
Syntax: /mutehistory (target)
Description: View a players mute history

~~~ mutestatus ~~~
Permission: mutesystem.mutestatus
Syntax: /mutestatus (target)
Description: View a players mute status

~~~ tempmute ~~~
Permission: mutesystem.tempmute
Syntax: /mute (target) (duration) [reason]
Description: Temporary mute a player
Information: The duration argument accepts a natural number followed by a time unit (the short time unit: m, h, d, w, M, y). You can have as many natural number time unit combinations as you want. However there must be no space in between. Example: 5d6h, 5d, 1y6M3w, 30m
Time units:
 - m = minute
 - h = hour
 - d = day
 - w = week
 - M = month
 - y = year

~~~ unmute ~~~
Permission: mutesystem.unmute
Syntax: /unmute (target)
Description: Unmute a player



